	   <tr><td colspan=2>High Elves make fine Wizards.&nbsp;&nbsp;They really don't have any serious disadvantages compared to the other Wizard races (their intelligence is a bit lower than others, but this is easily fixed with items and INT after 200 is generally just there to be there), although High Elves as a whole are bad at carrying lots of loot due to their low strength.  Generally, in EverQuest, pick whatever race suits you the best aesthetically.  You're going to be with that character for a LONG time...it's important to be satisfied with your choice.<br><br>Magicians are generally much better soloists than Wizards throughout their lives, but Wizards can solo well through the use of SoW Potions or Journeyman's Boots after level 29.  A Magician will ALWAYS have less of a risk factor when soloing, assuming the Magician and the Wizard are on the same level item-wise.<br><br>If you do decide to be a Magician however, don't become a part of what seems a trend for Magicians to whine on forums.  No offense to any of the good Magicians out there.<br><br>...By the way, I'm a Dark Elf Wizard.  Love the class to death.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>--Mennelkir Callistius,<br>The Unofficial Dark Elf of Tunare</td></tr>
